<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>Crontab - Tag - TyrangYang_Blog</title><link>https://tyrangyang.github.io/TyrangYang_blog/tags/crontab/</link><description>Crontab - Tag - TyrangYang_Blog</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 23 Jan 2020 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://tyrangyang.github.io/TyrangYang_blog/tags/crontab/" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Crontab overview</title><link>https://tyrangyang.github.io/TyrangYang_blog/crontab/</link><pubDate>Thu, 23 Jan 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>Haolin Yang</author><guid>https://tyrangyang.github.io/TyrangYang_blog/crontab/</guid><description><![CDATA[<h2 id="what-is-crontab">What is crontab</h2>
<p>Crontab is a toll to schedule commands. You can run your terminal command on a specific schedule like run a command every day or every weekends.</p>
<h2 id="basic-command">Basic command</h2>
<p>crontab [-u <em>user</em>] {-l | -e | -r}</p>
<table>
  <thead>
      <tr>
          <th style="text-align: center">command</th>
          <th style="text-align: center">utility</th>
      </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
      <tr>
          <td style="text-align: center">-l</td>
          <td style="text-align: center">list your cron job</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
          <td style="text-align: center">-r</td>
          <td style="text-align: center">remove your cron job</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
          <td style="text-align: center">-e</td>
          <td style="text-align: center">edit your cron job</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
          <td style="text-align: center">-u</td>
          <td style="text-align: center">specific a user</td>
      </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<h2 id="how-to-schedule-a-command">How to schedule a command</h2>
<p>Cron job looks like:</p>
<div class="code-block code-line-numbers open" style="counter-reset: code-block 0">
